a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.00c6bc62-b24a-4b8a-8a89-b2489e34301d.description=
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The path to check.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success - The operation succeeded.
a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.03ba0f82-68e4-40a7-8a49-fea4a1483e2b.prompt=Enter a starting directory a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.1c931512-f7f4-4b38-8593-a1be7e91e059.prompt=Enter the date (mm/dd/yyyy hh\:mm\:ss) \: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.3024aa71-86e9-4a1a-abfe-8c2d3fa6df60.prompt=Enter a value for list a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.4ab433cc-5400-42c8-88db-331698ef7bab.description=
Gets a list of one or more Elements in a list that match a given filter.

Inputs\:
list - the list to search.
delimiter - The delimiter that separates elements in list.
compareTo - The string to compare each element in the list against.
matchType - The type of match to perform.

Responses\:
success - 1 or more elements were found that matched.
failure - no elements matched, or something went wrong.

Returns\:
A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.

Results\:
others - all elements that did not match
matches - A delimiter delimited list of elements that match the rule.

Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Returns\: The value in the specified key. Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.927f0bae-df80-4b04-8ca6-553c7a403484.prompt=Enter the path\: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.a65d02a9-7b48-4109-a7d6-a99fa7f76e1f.prompt=Enter the extension (Eg. txt, xls, etc.) \: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.a9343ddb-e7e4-4412-8a30-10df59837358.transition.description=The given path is not a directory. a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.b0f5b752-fbbd-42fb-b3ba-c904dfa378e4.prompt=Enter the host where the files to be zipped are\: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.bd9161c6-f163-42fa-bf6f-1587d094ebbf.description=
This operation creates a UNC path given a host and a normal path. This operation does not check the validity of the given path or the existence of the given host. 

Input Parameters\:
host - the host to which the path refers to.
path - a path that will be converted to UNC.

Returns\:
The corresponding UNC path for the given host and path.

Responses\:
failure - the conversion to UNC failed
success - the conversion to UNC succeeded.
a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.bfba7fd3-c7b2-4b04-a946-2728ebae2b84.prompt=Enter the directory in which to zip \: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.c5a42c18-3987-43d2-9de7-2d50689922b5.prompt=Give a username\: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.cbda06a9-9e10-47f2-9785-a27051850cad.description=
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.
a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.d4e87acd-03d3-4665-a113-2dafeafafca4.prompt=Enter a value for password a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.d5a71daa-84af-4714-8214-a1b91e2f6c2c.prompt=Enter the host\: a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.d8eb1fce-a854-4699-adfe-b4993ea25955.transition.description=The directory ${directory} has no children with the extension ${extension}. a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.description=
To zip files with specified extension in a remote machine with an optional date input.

Inputs \:
host		- Host of the files to be zipped.
directory		- Path of the folder in which the zip operation has to be performed.
extension		- Extension of the files that have to be zipped.
time		- The date before which the files have to be zipped. (this input is an optional one).
user		- User credentials of the system in which the zip operation has to be performed.
password		- Password of the particular user in the system in which the zip operation has to be performed.
archiveName		-The name of the archive to be created.

Responses \:
success		- if the desired zip operation performed successfully.
failure		- any error occurs while executing  the flow.

Note \:
If the flow fails due to the non-availability of vjslib.dll,vjredist.exe has to be installed to continue the action which can be downloaded from the following link.

http\://msdn.microsoft.com/vjsharp/downloads/howtoget/default.aspx
a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.dff21fe5-6bda-401c-adbf-0bd0c389fdf2.description=
Zips a selected file.

Inputs\:
source - The file or folder to zip up.
destination - The full path/name of the zip file to create with the extension '.zip'.
deleteSource - A boolean value specifying whether Source should be deleted.
overwrite - A boolean value specifying whether the destination should be overwritten if it exists.
storeFullPath - A boolean value specifying whether the full path of the file should be stored in the zip.
username - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host during zip operation.
password - Password for username.

Responses\:
success - Source successfully zipped.
failure - Something went wrong.

Note\:
This operation runs only if the Visual J\# Library (found in vjslib.dll file) which corresponds to the installed .NET Framework is present on the RAS computer. This library should be added to the runtime environment. The desired Visual J\# Redistributables Package and more details about the installation process can be found at 
http\://www.microsoft.com/downloads/browse.aspx?displaylang\=en&productID\=643A97BE-7045-4736-9DD1-1A7366CDAA31
a81c6b9b-6c80-4de4-948a-cb360eac29da.f6942b32-7a48-480e-8487-6deaa8a9e8ec.transition.description=The children of ${directory} were retrieved successfully.
